# AKOS Collaborator Share

Use this rule whenever authoring a `COLLABORATOR_SHARE_REGISTRY` row,
running an engagement settlement, OR ratifying a commercial deviation
(rate excursion / share-split deviation / bill_mode deviation /
overlay-pct deviation). Codifies operator decisions **D-IH-86-DA**
(doctrine mint), **D-IH-86-DB** (TRUE-MARGIN formula), **D-IH-86-DC**
(clause table schema), **D-IH-86-DE** *(superseded)* (pre-rewrite
3-shape `share_pattern` enum + CS-08; superseded by D-IH-86-EJ at
Wave R+2), **D-IH-86-EJ** (4-base + 1-overlay rewrite ratified
2026-05-26 post-13/05-transcript substrate audit), **D-IH-86-EK**
(methodology-readiness axis + `parallel_invoice_stream_indicator`
boolean + CS-09 NEW), **D-IH-86-EL** (SUEZ recommercialization
to `consulting_direct + bd_commission_overlay`; supersedes D-IH-86-EG),
**D-IH-86-EM** (Stage-1 reset to charter; supersedes D-IH-86-DF
active-promotion), and **D-IH-86-EN** (methodology-readiness ×
share_pattern coherence gating; ratified at this Commit 4 governance
authoring layer). Mechanical companion to
[`COLLABORATOR_SHARE_DOCTRINE.md`](../../docs/references/hlk/v3.0/Admin/O5-1/People/canonicals/COLLABORATOR_SHARE_DOCTRINE.md).

This rule does **not** define the doctrine — that lives in the canonical.
This rule names the mechanical bar future agents and operators inherit
by default when touching any collaborator-share artifact.

## When this rule applies

A collaborator-share workflow is in scope for this rule when **any** of:

- An engagement involving a strategic collaborator opens / closes a
  milestone / closes final.
- A new row lands in any of the 5 collaborator-share canonical CSVs.
- A commercial deviation (rate excursion / share-split deviation /
  bill_mode deviation) is proposed for ratification.
- A settlement statement is generated for any engagement.
- A `custom`-pattern engagement requires the operator-defined
  commercial narrative.

Out of scope: pure cap-table partnerships (equity instead of revenue
share — use `eng_model_investor_advisor` engagement model); pure
milestone-class consulting with no collaborator (use
`eng_model_milestone_consultant`); internal Holistika employment
compensation (covered by payroll, not this discipline).

## RULE 1 — Resolve `share_pattern` + `share_overlay` + `methodology_readiness` BEFORE drafting any SHARE_REGISTRY row (binding)

Per D-IH-86-EJ + D-IH-86-EK + D-IH-86-EN, every SHARE_REGISTRY row
carries THREE load-bearing routing values that together determine the
validator's per-row math + audit branching:

- **`share_pattern`** (4-value enum) — the commercial shape of the engagement.
- **`share_overlay`** (1-value enum + NULL) — the optional stackable BD-commission slice.
- **`methodology_readiness`** (4-value enum) — the collaborator-capability shape that gates which patterns are appropriate (per §2.4 of the doctrine).

These are NOT interchangeable; the wrong triple produces silent math
errors at settlement OR a methodology-incoherent assignment that
collapses into the "35% compromise" failure mode the operator named
verbatim at the 2026-05-22 framing (*"i don't lie ... we lose value if
we don't have things ready because in reality A was correct"*). Resolve
via inline-ratify `AskQuestion` gate per
[`akos-inline-ratification.mdc`](akos-inline-ratification.mdc) BEFORE
authoring any SHARE_REGISTRY row.

### The 4 base `share_pattern` values (mutually exclusive per row)

| `share_pattern` | When to pick | Worked precedent |
|:---|:---|:---|
| `deep_partner_65_35` | Holistika contributes the full methodology + machinery + execution stack as the value of its 65% share; collaborator brings the deal + operates the process inside the methodology; B2B partner narrative. Requires `methodology_trained` OR `methodology_in_progress` (with mentoring clause). | Websitz / Rushly engagement (live 2026). |
| `bd_intro_only` | Collaborator brings a project but does NOT work on it operationally; collaborator is `methodology_naive` or `methodology_not_applicable`. Default 85/15 per-row (Holistika 85 + collaborator 15 BD-commission). | Pure-intro engagements; industry-association reference passes. |
| `joint_venture_aventure` | Peer-equivalent JV where both parties contribute substantial methodology stacks; both `methodology_trained` OR cross-recognize each other's stacks; shared upside AND shared downside. Default 50/50 per-row. | Future sister-consultancy or aligned-tooling-vendor co-deliveries; no current lived instantiation. |
| `consulting_direct` *(default 100/0)* | Holistika delivers an engagement as a direct consultancy (founder + execution team bill transparently); no operational collaborator party OR collaborator is BD-overlay-only (see RULE 6). | SUEZ POC corrected at Commit 5 — `consulting_direct + bd_commission_overlay` per D-IH-86-EL. |

### The 1 `share_overlay` value (stackable on `consulting_direct` or `deep_partner_65_35`)

| `share_overlay` | Pairs with | When to pick |
|:---|:---|:---|
| `bd_commission_overlay` *(default 15%)* | `consulting_direct` ✓ (primary use case); `deep_partner_65_35` ✓ (rare; external BD party intros a deal Holistika + a separate deep partner delivers); **NEVER** with `bd_intro_only` (circular — base IS the BD shape) or `joint_venture_aventure` (conflates symmetry with intro asymmetry — file as separate engagement OR reclassify base). | An intro/BD-only party brought a deal Holistika delivers; the operational delivery party (per base pattern) is unaffected — overlay party receives `bd_commission_pct` of the BENEFITS pool. Default 15%; deviation requires `COLLABORATOR_RATE_OVERRIDES` row with `override_kind=overlay_pct_deviation`. |

### The methodology-readiness × share_pattern coherence gate (NEW per D-IH-86-EN)

Every SHARE_REGISTRY row carries one `methodology_readiness` value of
4 (per doctrine §2.4). The coherence table names which patterns each
readiness value can take; mis-pairings produce a CS-09 FAIL finding:

| `methodology_readiness` | Eligible `share_pattern` | Hard-disqualified |
|:---|:---|:---|
| `methodology_trained` | all 4 | — |
| `methodology_in_progress` | `deep_partner_65_35` (with mentoring clause); `consulting_direct + bd_commission_overlay`; `bd_intro_only` | `joint_venture_aventure` (JV requires peer-equivalence) |
| `methodology_naive` | `bd_intro_only`; `consulting_direct + bd_commission_overlay` | `deep_partner_65_35` (forces the "35% compromise" failure mode); `joint_venture_aventure` |
| `methodology_not_applicable` | `bd_intro_only` | `deep_partner_65_35`; `joint_venture_aventure`; `consulting_direct` w/o overlay |

This is the structural prevention of the operator's verbatim 2026-05-22
framing: a `methodology_naive` collaborator placed on
`deep_partner_65_35` produces the "35% compromise" — Holistika carries
all the methodology burden but the partner's share has already been
fixed at 35% as if they brought commensurate value. CS-09 makes that
mis-pairing impossible to commit silently.

## RULE 2 — Co-mint the 5 CSV rows in the same commit (binding)

Per [`akos-holistika-operations.mdc`](akos-holistika-operations.mdc)
canonical-CSV gate discipline, every engagement application of this
doctrine touches up to 5 CSVs:

1. `COLLABORATOR_MARKET_RATE_REFERENCE.csv` — seed row if missing.
2. `PARTNER_OVERLAP_EXCLUSION_CLAUSES.csv` — append new clauses if any.
3. `HOLISTIKA_VENDOR_SERVICES_BILLED.csv` — 10 rows (one per service class).
4. `COLLABORATOR_SHARE_REGISTRY.csv` — base + overlay row count depends on
   the engagement's `(share_pattern, share_overlay)` triple:
   - `deep_partner_65_35` alone: 1 base row + (1 overlay row IF a separate
     BD-only party intros the deal).
   - `bd_intro_only` alone: 1 base row (no overlay allowed; base IS the BD shape).
   - `joint_venture_aventure` alone: 2+ base rows (one per JV peer);
     no overlay allowed.
   - `consulting_direct` alone: 1 base row (Holistika 100%; no operational
     collaborator).
   - `consulting_direct + bd_commission_overlay` (the SUEZ shape): 1 base
     row (Holistika 100% before overlay) + 1 overlay row per BD-overlay party.
5. `COLLABORATOR_RATE_OVERRIDES.csv` — append override rows for any
   ratified deviation (`market_rate_excursion` /
   `share_split_deviation` / `bill_mode_deviation` /
   `overlay_pct_deviation` NEW per D-IH-86-EJ).

Plus a DECISION_REGISTER row per ratified deviation OR per
methodology-readiness coherence override (when an operator explicitly
ratifies an in-progress `methodology_in_progress` on `deep_partner_65_35`
with a mentoring clause, that ratification needs a decision row even
though CS-09 passes). All rows land in the SAME commit; never commit a
SHARE_REGISTRY row standalone without its supporting VENDOR_SERVICES_BILLED
roster + overlay rows + DECISION_REGISTER rows (CS-02 / CS-03 / CS-04 /
CS-09 FAIL otherwise).

## RULE 3 — Run CS-01..CS-09 validator before commit (binding)

`py scripts/validate_collaborator_share.py` runs at every
`py scripts/verify.py pre_commit` invocation via
`validate_collaborator_share_self_test` step in
[`config/verification-profiles.json`](../../config/verification-profiles.json).
The full sweep (`py scripts/validate_collaborator_share.py` without
`--self-test`) runs before any commit touching the 5 CSVs OR the
doctrine OR the SOP.

The 9 checks are defined in
[`COLLABORATOR_SHARE_DOCTRINE.md`](../../docs/references/hlk/v3.0/Admin/O5-1/People/canonicals/COLLABORATOR_SHARE_DOCTRINE.md) §6:

| # | Check | Severity | Branches on `share_pattern` / `share_overlay`? |
|:--|:---|:---|:---|
| 1 | CS-01 — CSV header sha | FAIL | No |
| 2 | CS-02 — Cross-CSV FK integrity | FAIL | No |
| 3 | CS-03 — split-sum invariant audit (unified across-rows per engagement) | FAIL | **YES** (unified across-rows sum-to-100 per engagement_id; overlay rows count toward the engagement total — overlay slice deducted from base party's share so the engagement still sums to 100 per D-IH-86-EJ §6.3). |
| 4 | CS-04 — default-split + market-rate audit (composition-based) | WARN | **YES** (per-base anchor: 65/35 for `deep_partner_65_35`; 85/15 for `bd_intro_only`; 50/50 for `joint_venture_aventure`; 100/0 for `consulting_direct`; ±25% market-rate band; overlay-anchor 15% on top per D-IH-86-EJ §6.4). |
| 5 | CS-05 — bill_mode default audit | WARN | No (pattern-agnostic VENDOR_SERVICES_BILLED discipline). |
| 6 | CS-06 — Partner-overlap clause linkage | WARN | No. |
| 7 | CS-07 — Rate override expiry hygiene | INFO | No. |
| 8 | CS-08 — share_pattern + share_overlay enum validity *(supersedes D-IH-86-DE 3-value CS-08 per D-IH-86-EJ)* | FAIL | N/A (this check enforces both enums — base 4-value + overlay 1-value + NULL). |
| 9 | CS-09 — overlay-base pairing + methodology-pattern coherence *(NEW per D-IH-86-EK + D-IH-86-EN)* | FAIL | **YES** (overlay-base pairing per VALID_OVERLAY_BASE_PAIRINGS lookup + methodology_readiness × share_pattern coherence per RULE 1 coherence table). |

CS-03 + CS-04 + CS-09 branching is critical: a row authored under the
wrong `(share_pattern, share_overlay, methodology_readiness)` triple
will pass the wrong invariant audit and silently produce incorrect
settlement math AND/OR force the "35% compromise" failure mode.

## RULE 4 — Inline-ratify every commercial deviation (binding)

Per [`akos-inline-ratification.mdc`](akos-inline-ratification.mdc) +
[`inline-ratify-craft`](../skills/inline-ratify-craft/SKILL.md), every
proposed commercial deviation surfaces as an `AskQuestion` gate before
authoring the override + decision row. The 5-option enum for
disposition:

1. **ratify-as-proposed** — operator accepts the proposed deviation;
   author the override + DECISION_REGISTER row.
2. **ratify-with-amendment** — operator accepts with a tweak; author
   the amended override.
3. **defer-to-next-milestone** — defer the deviation to a future
   ratification window; OPS_REGISTER row.
4. **reject-keep-default** — operator rejects the deviation; no override
   row authored; row stays at default 65/35 OR pattern-specific anchor.
5. **escalate-to-blocker-tracker** — operator needs more time than the
   inline-ratify window allows; mint
   `docs/wip/planning/_blockers/<slug>-tracker.md` per
   [`akos-conflict-surfacing-and-blocker-trackers.mdc`](akos-conflict-surfacing-and-blocker-trackers.mdc).

Time-box recovery (24h+ silence + clean validators + reversible
disposition auto-defaults) applies only to reversible deviations
(`bill_mode_deviation`, expired rate override). Irreversible deviations
(commercial share-split deviation signed by collaborator;
`custom`-pattern commercial narrative committed to engagement folder)
NEVER auto-default — halt and escalate.

## RULE 5 — INFO → FAIL ramp gates on per-base + overlay coverage (binding)

The validator launches at INFO advisory for all 9 checks. The Wave R+2
doctrine rewrite (D-IH-86-EJ / EK / EL / EM) RESET Stage 1 from `active`
back to `charter` per D-IH-86-EM, because the prior Stage-1 promotion
(D-IH-86-DF) had been ratified on a worked example (SUEZ POC) whose
commercial classification was wrong (`orchestration_broker_thin_margin`
instead of `consulting_direct + bd_commission_overlay`). Promotion now
happens in two restarted stages per the operator's 2026-05-26 *"build
this properly with the rewrite first, then promote on real evidence"*
framing:

**Stage 1 — charter → active** (per doctrine §9; reset 2026-05-26):
- 1 corrected SUEZ POC settlement (Commit 5 of Wave R+2 doctrine rewrite)
  applies the doctrine end-to-end as `consulting_direct +
  bd_commission_overlay` with all 5 CSVs populated correctly.
- Validator CS-01..CS-09 PASS on the populated rows (including CS-09
  overlay-base pairing + methodology-readiness coherence).
- Operator-ratified re-active-promotion decision row (D-IH-86-EO or
  successor; reserved at Wave R+2 commit 1).

**Stage 2 — active → promoted-FAIL ramp** (gates):
- 3+ real engagements applying the doctrine cleanly with zero
  CS-01..CS-03 / CS-08 / CS-09 findings.
- **Per-base coverage requirement: ≥ 2 of the 4 base `share_pattern`
  values exercised in lived practice** (so the per-base branching has
  been tested beyond self-tests).
- **Overlay coverage requirement: ≥ 1 engagement exercising
  `bd_commission_overlay` cleanly** (so the overlay-stacking math has
  been validated against real bills).
- **Methodology-readiness coverage requirement: ≥ 2 of the 4
  `methodology_readiness` values exercised in lived practice** (so the
  CS-09 coherence gate has been tested across the spectrum, not only on
  one readiness shape).
- ≥ 1 cross-engagement audit pass at quarterly cadence with operator
  sign-off.
- Operator-ratified ramp-promotion decision row.
- CS-04 / CS-05 / CS-06 remain at WARN forever (judgment-class drift).
- CS-07 remains at INFO forever (cleanup hygiene).
- CS-01 / CS-02 / CS-03 / CS-08 / CS-09 promote to FAIL at every commit
  touching the 5 CSVs.

## RULE 6 — Overlay stacking discipline (NEW per D-IH-86-EJ §6.5)

The `bd_commission_overlay` is the ONLY overlay value in the current
enum. Future overlays (e.g., a hypothetical `affiliate_referral_overlay`
or `methodology_licensing_overlay`) must amend this doctrine + add a
new VALID_OVERLAY_BASE_PAIRINGS row + extend CS-09 before being
authored — silent additions are forbidden.

### Stacking rules (binding)

1. **At most ONE overlay row per base row.** A single engagement_id may
   carry multiple BD-overlay parties only if each parties their own
   `bd_commission_overlay` row pointing at the same base row; the
   aggregate overlay slice cannot exceed `bd_commission_pct_cap = 25`
   (per doctrine §2.3 cap to prevent benefits-pool drift). CS-03
   enforces the engagement-total-sum-to-100 invariant regardless of
   overlay count, so adding overlay parties mechanically deducts from
   the base party's slice (NOT from the customer-billed total).
2. **Overlay base pairing.** Per VALID_OVERLAY_BASE_PAIRINGS:
   `bd_commission_overlay` ONLY pairs with `consulting_direct` (primary
   use case) or `deep_partner_65_35` (rare; external BD party intros a
   deal Holistika + a separate deep partner deliver). NEVER pairs with
   `bd_intro_only` (the base IS the BD shape — overlay on top would be
   circular) or `joint_venture_aventure` (the JV is peer-symmetric;
   adding an asymmetric BD overlay collapses the symmetry — file as a
   separate engagement OR reclassify base).
3. **Overlay party identity ≠ base party identity.** An overlay row's
   `collaborator_id` must differ from the same engagement's base
   row(s)' `collaborator_id`. A collaborator cannot earn both a base
   share AND an overlay slice on the same engagement (the operator's
   *"don't double-bill the same party against itself"* framing from
   2026-05-26); when this is operationally what's intended, the
   collaborator's compensation belongs in the base row at a higher
   share_pct, not split across base + overlay.
4. **Overlay default 15% / deviation requires `overlay_pct_deviation`
   override row** in COLLABORATOR_RATE_OVERRIDES. The deviation must
   be ratified by an inline-AskQuestion gate per RULE 4 disposition
   enum — no silent overlay-pct authoring.
5. **Overlay `methodology_readiness` is locked to `methodology_naive`
   or `methodology_not_applicable`.** A BD-overlay party that is also
   `methodology_trained` or `methodology_in_progress` is structurally
   incoherent (they would qualify for `deep_partner_65_35` directly;
   shoehorning them into a BD-overlay slice underpays their
   contribution). CS-09 surfaces this as FAIL.

### Worked overlay example (SUEZ POC corrected commercial shape)

The SUEZ POC engagement at Commit 4 of Wave R+1 P3 was originally
authored as `orchestration_broker_thin_margin` (3 rows: Holistika 6 +
founder partner 50 + Aïsha 44). This shape was wrong per the 2026-05-26
transcript re-read: Aïsha is BD-overlay-only (intro party not
operating on the engagement); SUEZ's commercial relationship is direct
Holistika-consulting + Aïsha-BD-commission. The corrected shape per
D-IH-86-EL ships at Commit 5:

- 1 base row: `consulting_direct`, Holistika 85%, `methodology_trained`.
- 1 overlay row: `bd_commission_overlay`, Aïsha-Holistika-link 15%,
  `methodology_not_applicable`, `share_overlay=bd_commission_overlay`,
  `overlay_pct_deviation=NULL` (default 15%).
- Engagement total: 100% (CS-03 PASS).
- Methodology coherence: PASS (CS-09 PASS).

This worked example is the unblocker for Stage-1 re-active-promotion
per RULE 5 — without a clean SUEZ recommercialisation, the doctrine
stays at `charter` indefinitely.

## When this rule does NOT apply

- Pure cap-table partnerships (equity instead of revenue share) —
  governed by `eng_model_investor_advisor` instead.
- Pure milestone-class consulting with no collaborator party —
  governed by `eng_model_milestone_consultant` (Bâtard 2020 precedent).
- Internal Holistika team compensation — covered by employment
  contracts + payroll, not this discipline.
- Engagement folders where the operator explicitly does NOT involve a
  strategic collaborator AND no BD-overlay party intros the deal
  (single-vendor delivery — author as `consulting_direct` base row
  with no overlay).

